  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "mL51/k3ozgT84IXJsZFfcrVWyH8=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# Two-Package Monorepo Structure\n\nThe `bee-reactor-adaptor` repository is a pnpm monorepo with two publishable npm packages that split responsibilities between the core adapter library and the forked Connect host app.\n\n| Package | npm name | Role |\n|---------|----------|------|\n| `packages/adapter/` | `@liberuum-org/bee-reactor-adapter` | Core adapter: SwarmClient, SwarmChannel, encryption, feeds, stamps |\n| `packages/connect/` | `@liberuum-org/connect` | Fork of Connect with Swarm landing page + settings UI |\n\nThe adapter package is framework-agnostic and can in principle integrate into any Reactor-based host. The connect package is a Connect fork that consumes it and adds the Swarm-specific landing page plus settings UI (stamp management, storage stats, sync badges, folder tree, USD pricing).\n\nDevelopment uses `pnpm install` at the repo root, `pnpm build` to compile both, and `pnpm test` to run the 12-test E2E suite against a live `bee dev` node.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
    }
  },
